þe catte wol hete fyce bute a wol not chyeth þe water pha[

                    which follows; English portion all written on one line.

CamTCC1149.Transcription: Cat lufat viswch ac he nele his feth wete

BLHar2321.Transcription: The cat doth loue þe fishebut he will not wett her fate
BLHar2321.Note: This variant not rhyming; added to left margin by a later hand.

RylandsLat394.Transcription: The catt wolle fyssh ete but wol not here fote wete
RylandsLat394.Note:
Written all one line; translating ‘Cattus amat piscem sed non
                        vult tangere flumen’, which follows it.
